

24,May,2004


	 
      When we first arrived at Ohare airport in Chicago, Ill we reported to the USO lounge and signed in with the receptionist. Recruits arrived throughout the day from different parts of the country and even one from Puerto Rico. The recruit from Puerto Rico would eventually become the Recruit Cheif Petty Officer (RCPO) of our division, Rentas was his name. Eventually the staff from Great Lakes arrived to begin inprocessing. We sat down on the floor and filled out our graduation packets and put tags on our luggage. We also were issues our dog tags and our recruit pen. The recruit pen is a very important part of your daily uniform, it must hang on your dog tag chain along with the key to your seabag/AB drawer lock. If you are caught without your pen you will most likely be dropped. Another important thing to remember about your dog tags is to always keep them tucked into your shirt touching your skin. If you are caught with your dog tags outside of your shirt it wont be pretty. After finishing the some medical paperwork we were checked to ensure that our weight and height that are within standards. If you are over you will have your body fat taken at the airport. A few recruits were sent home for not meeting body fat requirements so make sure you are within standards before you go. 
     
    


